    {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "good_prompt",
      "prompt": "You are an empathetic HR Manager at a tech startup. Write a rejection email to a candidate who reached the final interview stage but was not selected. Maintain a professional yet warm tone, provide constructive feedback on their coding test, and encourage them to apply for future roles.",
      "response": "Subject: Update on Your Application for Software Engineer Position\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nWe appreciate the time you took to interview with us for the Software Engineer role at [Company Name]. We were impressed by your technical skills and experience, and we are grateful for the interest in our company.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we regret to inform you that we will not be moving forward with your application at this time. We were particularly impressed by your solutions to the coding challenges you presented in your technical assessment. Your understanding of [specific technology or concept] was impressive, but we felt that your approach to problem-solving in the final challenge did not align with our team's specific requirements.\n\nPlease know that this decision is not a reflection on your abilities or potential as a software engineer. We recognize that you have a lot to offer, and we encourage you to continue developing your skills and exploring opportunities that align with your strengths.\n\nWe will keep your application on file and would be happy to consider you for future roles that may be a better fit. We appreciate your interest in [Company Name] and wish you the best in your job search.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\nHR Manager",
